The paper deals with the problem of private record linkage, which involves matching records from two different databases without revealing any sensitive information. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and data structures (cs.DS). Given that the paper proposes a novel privacy model and protocols for solving the problem of private record linkage, it is likely to be relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, the emphasis on privacy and data protection suggests that cs.CR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.CY, and cs.DS.
